FBIS3-47885 "dreas014__a94029" FBIS-EAS-94-014-A Document Type:Daily Report 21 January 1994 ANNEX Japan Defense Official Wants Surveillance Satellites OW1801101694 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 18 Jan 94 Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW1801101694 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:BFN [Text] Noboru Hoshuyama, director of the Defense Agency [DA] Director General's Secretariat, speaking at a 17 January news conference on DA plans to procure surveillance satellites, said: "On the prerequisite that there are no political constraints, it is desirable to have surveillance satellites from the standpoint of improving intelligence capabilities." He thus indicated hopes that the DA would have such satellites in the future. Hoshuyama also admitted that "research and studies are being conducted on the usefulness of surveillance satellites" at various DA bureaus and departments and at staff offices of the Ground, Maritime, and Air Defense Forces.
